.TH DBX-VAULT 1 "2026-06-02" "dbx 0.30.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-vault \- manage credentials and encryption keys
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx vault set
.I host
.PP
.B dbx vault get
.I host
.PP
.B dbx vault delete
.I host
.PP
.B dbx vault list
.PP
.B dbx vault info
.PP
.B dbx vault set-encryption-key
.PP
.B dbx vault init-age
.SH DESCRIPTION
Store and retrieve credentials in the system keychain (macOS Keychain
on Darwin,
.B libsecret
on Linux), keeping passwords out of
.IR config.json .
.PP
Also manages encryption keys used by
.B dbx
backup encryption: the GPG passphrase or the
.BR age-encryption (1)
identity file.
.SH ACTIONS
.TP
.BI "set " host
Prompt for and store a password for
.IR host .
.TP
.BI "get " host
Print the stored password for
.IR host
(intended for piping).
.TP
.BI "delete " host
Remove the stored password for
.IR host .
.TP
.B list
List every host that has a stored password.
.TP
.B info
Show which backend is in use and where keys live.
.TP
.B set-encryption-key
Store the GPG passphrase used by
.IR encryption: gpg
backups.
.TP
.B init-age
Generate a fresh age identity at
.IR ~/.config/dbx/age.txt
(or honor
.BR DBX_AGE_KEY_FILE )
and update
.IR config.json
to use it.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
dbx vault set production
dbx vault list
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DBX_AGE_KEY_FILE
Override the default age identity file path.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dbx/age.txt
The age identity file (mode 600).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-host (1),
.BR age (1),
.BR gpg (1).
